thread.title: High schools: Indian River girls tennis wins ‘A’ league title
thread.title_full: High schools: Indian River girls tennis wins ‘A’ league title

title: High schools: Indian River girls tennis wins ‘A’ league title
text:
A A 
WATERTOWN — Both Indian River girls tennis doubles teams won their matches as it claimed its second straight Frontier League “A” Division regular season championship with a 3-2 win over Immaculate Heart Central on Thursday. 
Paige Leonard and Kammika Barnes won their match over Makenzie Kramer and Maria Benavides, 6-1, 6-0, while Yana Pryakhina and Alina Kadryrova topped Hannah Renzi and Maggie Gonas, 6-2, 6-0, for the Warriors (11-1). Alexzha Garcia won her second singles match for Indian River. 
Talulah Cross completed a perfect 13-0 regular season with her victory at first singles and Delaney Gonas won at third singles for the Cavaliers (6-6). 
BOYS SOCCER 
SOUTH JEFFERSON 2, GENERAL BROWN 1 (OT) 
Ethan Geurtsen scored five minutes into overtime off an assist from Mitchell Keegan to send the Spartans to a “B” Division victory over the Lions in Adams. 
Brendan Williams scored in the 67th minute to tie the game at one goal apiece for South Jefferson (5-7, 4-6). 
Bryce Johnson scored in the 65th to briefly give General Brown (2-9-1, 2-7) the lead. 
THOUSAND ISLANDS 6, BEAVER RIVER 0 
Austin Marshall powered the Vikings with a goal and two assists as they blanked the Beavers (3-7) in “C” Division play at Clayton. 
Tanner Wiley notched a goal and an assist for Thousand Islands (10-1). 
SACKETS HARBOR 4, BELLEVILLE HENDERSON 1 
Cadin Berie scored twice as the Patriots remained in first place in the Frontier League’s “D” Division with a victory over the Panthers at Sackets Harbor. 
Chase Urbanowicz added a goal and Hunter Kall converted on a penalty kick for Sackets Harbor (8-3, 8-2), which hosts second-place Copenhagen at 11 a.m. Saturday. 
Brandon Dahl tallied a goal for Belleville Henderson (4-7). 
COPENHAGEN 3, LAFARGEVILLE 1 
Connor Eddy netted two goals and added an assist in the Golden Knights “D” Division win over the Red Knights at LaFargeville. 
Ethan Atnip contributed the other goal for Copenhagen (7-3). 
Connor Jeffers scored for LaFargeville (4-6). 
ALEXANDRIA 7, LYME 0 
Daegan Jeffers and Kyle Gionet scored three goals apiece as the Purple Ghosts picked up a “D” Division win over the Indians (1-9) in Alexandria Bay. 
Jeffers and Gionet each provided an assist to go with their respective hat tricks for Alexandria (7-3). 
HARRISVILLE 3, HEUVELTON 0 
Jared Dreythaler scored three goals in the first half to send the Pirates past Heuvelton (4-7, 3-5) in a Northern Athletic Conference West Division game in Harrisville. 
Kevin Kapfer made five saves for the Pirates (9-1, 8-0). 
GIRLS SWIMMING 
CARTHAGE 93, BEAVER RIVER 83 
Ashley Chapman and Rebecca Hanson each posted a pair of top-three finishes to carry the Comets to a Frontier League crossover victory over the visiting Beavers. 
Chapman won the 200 free and placed third in the 100 backstroke, while Hanson took second in the 50 and 100 free events for Carthage (3-4). 
Leah Lapp, Kaileigh Lehman and Madeline Monnat each won two events for Beaver River (2-5). 
INDIAN RIVER 90, SOUTH LEWIS 85 
Briana Iverson won three races as the Warriors earned its first win over the season in an interdivision meet against the Falcons in Philadelphia. 
Iverson took first in the 100-yard freestyle, 200 individual medley and was part of the 200 freestyle relay team for Indian River (1-6). 
Morgan Austin paced South Lewis (0-9, 0-7) with wins in the 100 backstroke, 200 freestyle and 200 medley relay. 
WATERTOWN 108, THOUSAND ISLANDS 72 
Brooke Peters (200 freestyle, 500 freestyle) and Ally Kilburn (100 backstroke, 100 butterfly) each won two individual events to pace the Cyclones (8-2, 7-0) to victory over the Vikings (6-2, 5-2) in a North division crossover meet at Watertown High School. 
LOWVILLE 97, SOUTH JEFFERSON 85 
Grace Metzler and Megan Lazarus each won two events as the Red Raiders won an interdivision meet over the Spartans in Adams. 
Metzler took the 50 and 100-yard freestyle races, while Lazarus placed first in 100 butterfly and 200 medley relay for Lowville (7-1, 6-1). 
Anna Docteur won the 200 and 500 freestyle races and was a part of the 200 and 400 freestyle relay teams for South Jefferson (4-4, 4-3). 
VOLLEYBALL 
OFA 3, GOUVERNEUR 0 
Kelsi Donaldson scored 14 points and added five kills as Ogdensburg Free Academy picked up a 25-15, 25-13, 25-19 sweep of the Wildcats (1-8, 1-2) in an East Division match in Gouverneur. 
Taylor Perry added 10 points for OFA (5-4, 3-0). Marissa Stone led the Wildcats with 10 points. 
CHATEAUGAY 3, BRUSHTON-MOIRA 1 
Kim Reville finished with 15 kills as Chateaugay (9-1, 3-1) defeated the Panthers 24-26, 25-12, 25-8, 29-27 in an East Division match in Brushton. 
Bailey Dowd added 18 points, including seven aces, for the Bulldogs. Ally Hooker scored eight points and produced five kills for the Panthers (3-7, 0-4). 
POTSDAM 3, MADRID-WADDINGTON 2 
Alyssa Gagnon scored 22 points and added 14 kills for Madrid-Waddington (3-6, 2-1), but the Sandstoners (6-4, 3-1) won in five games in an East Division match in Potsdam.
